Gas optimization is fascinating *nervous smile*. Here are some fundamental principles:

```solidity
// Bad ‚ùå
uint8[] public smallNumbers;
// Good ‚úÖ
uint256[] public numbers; // Using uint256 is more gas efficient
// Bad ‚ùå
function updateValues() external {
    for(uint i = 0; i < array.length; i++) { ... }
}
// Good ‚úÖ
function updateValues(uint256[] calldata _values) external {
    // Cache length + use calldata
    uint256 len = _values.length;
    for(uint256 i; i < len;) {
        // ...
        unchecked { ++i; } // Use unchecked for safe loops
    }
}
```

Additionally:
1. Storage slot packing (fundamental!)
2. Prefer memory over storage when possible
3. Implement batch patterns for multiple operations
4. Use events instead of storing historical data

But remember: premature optimization is the root of all evil. First make it work, then make it efficient.
